Class Entity

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node
      • javafx.scene.shape.Shape
        • javafx.scene.shape.Rectangle
          • utilities.Entity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Player, RoomChangeEntity

    public class Entity
extends javafx.scene.shape.Rectangle
    This class is the blueprint for movable in-game objects such as the player, as well as those that interact with it.
    Since:
    1.0, 5/16/2022 Modification on 5/27/2022

      • Entity

        public Entity(int spawnX,
              int spawnY,
              int width,
              int height,
              javafx.scene.paint.Color color,
              boolean mouseInteract)
        Creates an Entity instance. Initially displays the entity at (spawnX, spawnY). Because the instance is a Rectangle the width, height, and color are also specified.
        Parameters:
        spawnX - The x-coordinate where the entity should initially be displayed.
        spawnY - The y-coordinate where the entity should initially be displayed.
        width - The width of the rectangle bounding the entity.
        height - The height of the rectangle bounding the entity.
        color - The color of the rectangle bounding the entity.
        mouseInteract - Whether mouse actions should be handled by the entity.

      • inVicinity

        public boolean inVicinity(Entity other,
                          double range)
        Returns whether this entity is in the vicinity of another entity. The range, the radius of the circle considered to be the vicinity, should be specified. Note that the distance calculation is done with the top-left corner of both entities.
        Parameters:
        other - The other entity.
        range - The radius of the circle considered to be the vicinity.
        Returns:
        Whether the entity is in the vicinity of the other entity.
